		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(center)">5</p>
				<p>accompany me.  We went&#8212;<persName>Dr. Henry</persName><lb/> I said will you answer me a few<lb/> questions&#63;  I want to be answered<lb/> exactly<add>&#63;</add>&#44; as on <hi rend="underline">your</hi> answers depend my<lb/> marriage with <persName>Mr. P.</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">If I marry <persName>Mr. P.</persName> can any one point<lb/> their finger at us in scorn and say<lb/> they have done wrongly&#63;  &#8220;In Madam.&#8221;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">If we marry and have children<lb/> are they legitimate&#63;  &#8220;Yes Madam&#8221;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Will any reproach be attached to<lb/> those children through our marriage&#63;<lb/> &#8220;No Madam&#8221;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Well&#44; what do you want Doctor&#63;<lb/>  I&#39;ll tell you what you <hi rend="underline">can</hi> do&#44; you<lb/> can go to <placeName>Germany</placeName> and get &#8220;Kalitza&#8221;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I indignantly answered &#8220;I will<lb/> see them further first&#8221; I was <hi rend="underline">so</hi><lb/> very angry.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Dr. Henry</persName> <hi rend="underline">then</hi> said &#8220;Now I <del>will</del><lb/> am going to take off my gown &#40;<add>&#63;</add><lb/> the action to the words&#41; and told you</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p rend="align(center)">6</p>
				<p><hi rend="underline">confidentially</hi> that had you <hi rend="underline">had</hi> Kalitza<lb/> you then dared not marry him.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I rose joyfully &#8220;Thank you Doctor<lb/> &#40;said I&#41; those news was an act of parliament<lb/> but what a coach and six<add>&#63;</add> could drive<lb/> through.  <persName>Mr. P.</persName> we will be married.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Dr. Henry</persName> said any Jewish mi&#45;<lb/>&#45;nister could marry us&#44; and we then<lb/> applied to the <persName>Revd. Dr. Eckman</persName> who<lb/> married us.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><hi rend="underline">If</hi> I have sinned&#44; which I hope<lb/> I have not&#44; it lays at <persName>Dr. Henry&#39;s</persName> door&#44;<lb/> for as I hope to meet my maker hereafter<lb/> I had resolved had he said <hi rend="underline">no</hi> I would<lb/> <hi rend="underline">not</hi> have married.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">The doctors&#39; refusal arose&#44; not as<lb/> <persName>Theophilus</persName> states from <persName>Dr. Henry&#39;s</persName><lb/> <hi rend="underline">conviction</hi> of wrong <hi rend="underline">but</hi> because of<lb/> in cabal suscitated<add>&#63;</add> by <persName>A. B. Ephraim</persName><lb/> and others against him to catch<lb/> him tripping</p>
				<p>&#42;&#42;&#42;</p>
				<p>P. S. I should feel regret at mentioning</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p rend="align(center)">7</p>
				<p><persName>Dr. Henry&#39;s</persName> confidential remarks to me&#44;<lb/> were it not that being so well acquainted<lb/> with the Doctor&#39;s Phraseology&#44; I feel but<lb/> little scruple in asserting that &#8220;<persName>Theophilus</persName>&#8221;<lb/> and the Doctor do not live <hi rend="underline">very</hi> far<lb/> apart.</p>
				<p rend="align(center)">&#42;&#42;&#42;</p>
		</body>
